disciplinary cooperating teams	Each Scrum team must have specific skills to successfully deliver the project.  By having each member with a broad but shallow understanding of many topics and a deep understanding of one or two topics (for which they will be considered the expert).  This type of ability/skill-set distribution is called a T-shaped skill set.  Enterprises always look for a T-shaped skill set model when selecting development team members.
